1. Create a volume.

aws ec2 create-volume --size 1 --availability-zone us-east-1a --volume-type gp2

2. Attach EBS Volume to a Running Instance.

ec2-attach-volume vol-7fbd3564 --instance i-97624766 --device /dev/sdf 

3. Prewarm the Volume

lsblk

sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/xvdf bs=1M
*Read-only: To pre-warm only previously written blocks

sudo dd if=/dev/xvdf of=/dev/xvdf conv=notrunc bs=1M
* Read-then-write-back: To pre-warm an entire restored volume

4. Create Filesystem on the attached volume and then mount the volume.

sudo file -s /dev/xvdf
sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf
sudo mkdir /ebs-volume
sudo mount /dev/xvdf /ebs-volume

sudo vi /etc/fstab

add the line
/dev/xvdf       /ebs-volume   ext4    defaults,nofail        0       2


5. Create a snapshot of all the volumes.







